  "ExecutionTrace": [
    "Step 0: Idle",
    "Step 1: Thinking\n  [{ Id = edb37d45-a0d2-4011-a692-3817ea0204f6\n     CorrelationId = CorrelationId 1bfc4ff8-5ffb-4109-8fef-27c9780d39f5\n     Sender = System\n     Receiver = Some (Agent (AgentId 1e5856a9-d9ed-4b54-adbe-7ec4f285ff23))\n     Performative = Request\n     Intent = Some Coding\n     Constraints = { MaxTokens = None\n                     MaxComplexity = None\n                     Timeout = None\n                     KnowledgeBoundary = [] }\n     Ontology = None\n     Language = \u0022text\u0022\n     Content =\n      \u0022### Summary of F# Program for Transcription and Summarization\n\n**Goal:** Create an F# program to automate the transcription and summarization of audio recordings using a large language model.\n\n**Constraints:**\n1. The program should take an audio file as input.\n2. It should transcribe the audio into text using a large language model.\n3. The program should then generate a summary of the key points discussed in the recording.\n\n**Validation Criteria:**\n- Successfully transcribe the audio and produce a coherent summary of the content.\n- The summary should capture the main ideas without being overly verbose.\n\n**Available Tools:**\nThe program will use various tools to achieve its goal, including:\n- \u0060http_get\u0060: To fetch necessary data or configurations.\n- \u0060save_note\u0060: To save intermediate results or notes.\n- \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060: For evaluating F# code snippets.\n- \u0060fetch_webpage\u0060: To extract text from webpages if needed.\n- \u0060record_metric\u0060: To record performance metrics.\n- \u0060report_status\u0060: To provide a status report of the tools.\n\n**Steps to Implement:**\n1. **Transcription**: Use a large language model to transcribe the audio file into text.\n2. **Summarization**: Generate a summary of the transcribed text using another large language model or summarization tool.\n3. **Validation**: Ensure the summary is coherent and captures key points.\n\n**Implementation Plan:**\n1. **Read Audio File**: Use \u0060read_file\u0060 to read the audio file.\n2. **Transcription**: Use an external service or API that supports audio transcription (e.g., Google Cloud Speech-to-Text) via HTTP request with \u0060http_get\u0060.\n3. **Summarization**: Use a summarization tool or model to generate a summary of the transcribed text.\n4. **Save and Validate**: Save the summary using \u0060save_note\u0060 and validate it for coherence.\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- If transcription fails, use \u0060record_metric\u0060 to log the error and attempt a retry with exponential backoff using \u0060retry_with_backoff\u0060.\n- If summarization fails, similarly log the error and attempt a different approach or tool.\n\n**Final Output:**\nThe program will output the transcribed text and the generated summary in a structured format, ensuring it meets the validation criteria.\n\n### Example Code Snippet (Pseudo-F#)\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet transcribeAudio audioFilePath =\n    // Use http_get to call transcription API with audio file content\n    let response = http_get { url = \u0022https://api.transcription.com/transcribe\u0022; body = audioFilePath }\n    response.text\n\nlet summarizeText text =\n    // Use fsharp_eval or another tool to generate a summary\n    let summary = fsharp_eval { code = $\u0022summarize \\\u0022{text}\\\u0022\u0022 }\n    summary.result\n\nlet main audioFilePath =\n    try\n        let transcribedText = transcribeAudio audioFilePath\n        let summary = summarizeText transcribedText\n        save_note { key = \u0022transcription\u0022; content = transcribedText }\n        save_note { key = \u0022summary\u0022; content = summary }\n        printfn \u0022Transcription and Summary: %s\u0022 summary\n    with\n    | ex -\u003E\n        record_metric { name = \u0022error_transcription\u0022; value = 1.0 }\n        printfn \u0022Error during transcription or summarization: %s\u0022 ex.Message\n\n// Example usage\nmain \u0022path/to/audio/file.wav\u0022\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nThis pseudo-code outlines the steps to transcribe an audio file and generate a summary using F# and the available tools. The program handles errors gracefully and logs metrics for monitoring.\u0022\n     Timestamp = 2025-12-28 8:53:07 AM\n     Metadata = map [] }]",
